{"questionId":"12276","questionHtml":"<p>Given that<strong><em> A</em></strong> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  3&amp;{ - 2} \\\\   { - 3}&amp;4  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <strong><em>I</em></strong> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1&amp;0 \\\\   0&amp;1  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, find the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\lambda \">\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n</math></span> for which&nbsp;(<strong><em>A</em> </strong>– <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\lambda \">\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n</math></span><em><strong>I</strong></em>) is a singular matrix.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>singular matrix ⇒ det = 0<strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (R1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left| {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {3 - \\lambda }&amp;{ - 2} \\\\   { - 3}&amp;{4 - \\lambda }  \\end{array}} \\right|\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mi>λ</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mi>λ</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>|</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {3 - \\lambda } \\right)\\left( {4 - \\lambda } \\right) - 6 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {\\lambda ^2} - 7\\lambda&nbsp; + 6 = 0\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\lambda&nbsp; = 1\">\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> or 6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong><strong><em>(A1)&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;(C6)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong><em>&nbsp;</em>Award <em><strong>(C2)</strong></em> for one correct answer with no working.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12276","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.47","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that A = ( 3 − 2 − 3 4 ) and I = ( 1 0 0 1 ) , find the values of λ for which (A – λ I) is a singular matrix.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"47","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}